Document: AudioEffectLowShelfFilter
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectlowshelffilter.rst
Summary: A low-shelf filter that controls the gain of all frequencies below a specified cutoff frequency, used to adjust the low-end strength of a sound.

A "low-shelf" filter controls the gain of all frequencies below AudioEffectFilter.cutoff_hz. This filter can be used to adjust the "strength" of a sound, by increasing or decreasing its low-end.
